{META_DATA}: INCEPTION
{META_DATA}: Written by
{META_DATA}: Christopher Nolan
{META_DATA}: FADE IN:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DAWN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CRASHING SURF.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The waves TOSS a BEARDED MAN onto wet sand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He lies there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A CHILD'S SHOUT makes him LIFT his head to see: a LITTLE BLONDE BOY crouching, back towards us, watching the tide eat a SANDCASTLE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A LITTLE BLONDE GIRL joins the boy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Bearded Man tries to call them, but they RUN OFF, FACES UNSEEN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He COLLAPSES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The barrel of a rifle ROLLS the Bearded Man onto his back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A JAPANESE SECURITY GUARD looks down at him, then calls up the beach to a colleague leaning against a JEEP.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Behind them is a cliff, and on top of that, a JAPANESE CASTLE.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ELEGANT DINING ROOM, JAPANESE CASTLE - LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Security Guard waits as an ATTENDANT speaks to an ELDERLY JAPANESE MAN sitting at the dining table, back to us.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ATTENDANT
{META_DATA}: (in Japanese)
{DIALOGUE}: He was delirious.
{DIALOGUE}: But he asked for you by name.
{DIALOGUE}: And...
{META_DATA}: (to the Security Guard)
{DIALOGUE}: Show him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SECURITY GUARD
{META_DATA}: (in Japanese)
{DIALOGUE}: He was carrying nothing but this...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He puts a HANDGUN on the table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Elderly Man keeps eating.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SECURITY GUARD
{DIALOGUE}: ...and this.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Security Guard places a SMALL PEWTER CONE alongside the gun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Elderly Man STOPS eating.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Picks up the cone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELDERLY JAPANESE MAN
{META_DATA}: (in Japanese)
{DIALOGUE}: Bring him here.
{DIALOGUE}: And some food.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SAME - MOMENTS LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Elderly Man watches the Bearded Man WOLF down his food.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He SLIDES the handgun down the table towards him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELDERLY JAPANESE MAN
{META_DATA}: (in English)
{DIALOGUE}: Are you here to kill me?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Bearded Man glances up at him, then back to his food.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 2.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Elderly Japanese Man picks up the cone between thumb and forefinger.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELDERLY JAPANESE MAN
{DIALOGUE}: I know what this is.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He SPINS it onto a table- it CIRCLES gracefully across the polished ebony... a SPINNING TOP.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELDERLY JAPANESE MAN
{DIALOGUE}: I've seen one before.
{DIALOGUE}: Many, many years ago...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Elderly Japanese Man STARES at the top mesmerized.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELDERLY JAPANESE MAN
{DIALOGUE}: It belonged to a man I met in a half-remembered dream...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVE IN on the GRACEFULLY SPINNING TOP...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELDERLY JAPANESE MAN
{DIALOGUE}: A man possessed of some radical notions...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Elderly Japanese Man STARES, remembering...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: What's the most resilient parasite?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SAME ELEGANT DINING ROOM - NIGHT (YEARS EARLIER)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The speaker, COBB, is 35, handsome, tailored.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A young Japanese man, SAITO, eats as he listens.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: A bacteria?
{DIALOGUE}: A virus?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb gestures at their feast with his wine glass-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: An intestinal worm?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saito's fork pauses, mid-air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb GRINS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A third man is at the table- ARTHUR.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He jumps in to save the pitch-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: What Mr. Cobb is trying to say-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: An idea.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saito looks at Cobb, curious.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 3.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Resilient, highly contagious.
{DIALOGUE}: Once an idea's taken hold in the brain it's almost impossible to eradicate.
{DIALOGUE}: A person can cover it up, ignore it- but it stays there.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAITO
{DIALOGUE}: But surely-to forget...?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Information, yes.
{DIALOGUE}: But an idea?
{DIALOGUE}: Fully formed, understood?
{DIALOGUE}: That sticks...
{META_DATA}: (taps forehead)
{DIALOGUE}: In there, somewhere.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAITO
{DIALOGUE}: For someone like you to steal?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: Yes.
{DIALOGUE}: In the dream state, conscious defenses are lowered and your thoughts become vulnerable to theft.
{DIALOGUE}: It's called extraction.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: But, Mr. Saito, we can train your subconscious to defend itself from even the most skilled extractor.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAITO
{DIALOGUE}: How can you do that?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Because I am the most skilled extractor.
{DIALOGUE}: I know how to search your mind and find your secrets.
{DIALOGUE}: I know the tricks, and I can teach them to your subconscious so that even when you're asleep, your guard is never down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb leans forwards.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Holding Saito's gaze.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: But if I'm going to help you, you have to be completely open to me.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll need to know my way around your thoughts better than your wife, your analyst, anyone.
{META_DATA}: (gestures around)
{DIALOGUE}: If this is a dream and you've got a safe full of secrets, I need to know what's in that safe.
{DIALOGUE}: For this to work, you have to let me in.
{DIALOGUE}: 4.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saito gives this a flicker of a smile.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rises.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A BODYGUARD opens double doors which give onto a LAVISH PARTY.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAITO
{DIALOGUE}: Gentlemen.
{DIALOGUE}: Enjoy your evening as I consider your proposal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They watch Saito leave.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur turns to Cobb, worried-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: He knows.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb motions silence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A TREMOR starts, they steady their glasses, Cobb glances at his watch- THE SECOND HAND IS FROZEN.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: What's going on up there?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And we-
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FILTHY BATHROOM - DAY (FEELS LIKE DIFFERENT TIME)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb, ASLEEP, SITTING IN A CHAIR AT THE END OF A STEAMING BATH.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The chair is up on a cabinet- the bottom of the legs level with the rim of the tub.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A sweating man (40's) watches over Cobb.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This is NASH.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A distant EXPLOSION rumbles through the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nash moves to the window, parts the curtains.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Outside: a CHAOTIC DEVELOPING-WORLD CITY- the street filled with RIOTERS- SMASHING, BURNING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nash checks Cobb's left wrist: above his watch, tape holds TWO THIN YELLOW TUBES in place.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nash looks at Cobb's watch- THE SECOND HAND CRAWLS UNNATURALLY SLOWLY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nash follows the tubes to a SILVER BRIEFCASE at Arthur's feet: ARTHUR IS ASLEEP in an armchair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tubes connect the briefcase to Arthur's wrist.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nash follows another set of tubes from the briefcase to where they pass under the door to the bedroom.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Through the crack of the door, Nash sees SAITO ASLEEP on the bed, tubes running to his wrist.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BOOM- a closer EXPLOSION, and we-
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BULLET TRAIN COMPARTMENT - DAY (FEELS LIKE DIFFERENT TIME)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nash, ASLEEP.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Head ROCKING AGAINST THE WINDOW as the train BUMPS OVER A ROUGH PIECE OF TRACK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 5.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A Japanese Man, TODASHI (18) watches Nash nervously.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He checks Nash's wrist: TWO YELLOW TUBES CONNECT NASH WITH THREE OTHER SLEEPING MEN IN THE COMPARTMENT: COBB, ARTHUR, SAITO.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Todashi checks his watch: THE SECOND HAND TICKS IN REAL TIME.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another TRAIN PASSES in the opposite direction with a MIGHTY WHUMP- Todashi's eyes FLY to Nash's sleeping face-
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: NASH JERKS WITH THE MOVEMENT OF THE TRAIN, and we-
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FILTHY BATHROOM - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another EXPLOSION- Nash CHECKS the sleeping Cobb and we-
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. ROOFTOP TERRACES, JAPANESE CASTLE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A LOW TREMOR RUMBLES THROUGH THE CASTLE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb and Arthur steady themselves against the wooden rail.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Several TILES and pieces of MASONRY fall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Below them a BLACK SEA churns.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Other GUESTS wander the massive terraces.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: Saito knows.
{DIALOGUE}: He's playing with us.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: I can get it here.
{DIALOGUE}: The information's in the safe- he looked right at it when I mentioned secrets.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur nods.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then spots someone over Cobb's shoulder.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: What's she doing here, Cobb?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb turns to see a beautiful woman, elegantly dressed, staring out at the sea.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This is MAL.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb watches her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: You just get to your room.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll take care of the rest.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: See that you do.
{DIALOGUE}: We're here to work.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur brushes past Mal, shaking his head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She nears Cobb.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Looks out at the DROP.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The WIND WHIPS HER HAIR-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: If I jumped, would I survive?
{DIALOGUE}: 6.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: With a clean dive, perhaps.
{DIALOGUE}: Mal, why are you here?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns to look at him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Amused.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: I thought you might be missing me...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She smiles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He leans in, mesmerized.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: I am.
{DIALOGUE}: But I can't trust you anymore.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She stares up at him, inviting.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: So what?
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BEDROOM SUITE, JAPANESE CASTLE - MOMENTS LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mal sips champagne as she studies a painting by Francis Bacon.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: Looks like Arthur's taste.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb is looking down through the window at the GUARDS patrolling the castle at ground level.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Actually, Mr. Saito is partial to postwar British painters.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns to Mal, donning a pair of black leather gloves.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Would you sit down?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mal lowers herself gracefully into a leather wingback chair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb approaches, pulls out a length of BLACK ROPE and kneels at Mal's feet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks down at him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: Tell me...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb TIES the rope around the CHAIR LEGS.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: Do the children miss me?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb pauses.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He lets his gloved fingers lightly touch Mal's ankle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks up at her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 7.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: You can't imagine.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mal looks away, uncomfortable.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb gets to his feet, letting out the rope as he moves back to the window.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: What're you doing?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb tosses the rope out-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Getting some air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He tugs on the rope, testing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The weight of the chair, with Mal on it, holds.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Stay seated.
{DIALOGUE}: Please.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And with that, he JUMPS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mal considers the open window.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. JAPANESE CASTLE WALL - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb RAPPELS down the wall, darting past windows.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stops at a particular one.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gets out a glass cutter-
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly he starts DROPPING-
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BEDROOM SUITE, JAPANESE CASTLE - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The EMPTY CHAIR SLIDES across the floor- WEDGES under the window-
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. JAPANESE CASTLE WALL - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb JOLTS to a stop 15 ft. lower.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks up at the bedroom window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Shakes his head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Starts climbing back.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. KITCHEN, JAPANESE CASTLE - MOMENTS LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb drops silently from the window into the darkened kitchen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pulls a PISTOL from his belt, screwing a SILENCER onto the barrel as he GLIDES across the room.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HALL, JAPANESE CASTLE-CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb SLIPS through the shadows towards a GUARD stationed at the head of a GRAND STAIRCASE...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Guard HEARS something- TURNS- PEERS into the shadows...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb FLASHES out of the shadows, silenced pistol up, AIMING- 8.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PHHT- head shot- the Guard starts to drop... but Cobb is already there to CATCH him, sliding on his knees and lowering the Guard SILENTLY to the floor.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. DINING ROOM, JAPANESE CASTLE - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb moves to a PAINTING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With practiced hands he removes it from the wall, revealing a SAFE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb spins the dial, pulls it OPEN, GRABS an envelope from within, stuffs it into his waistband, where there is already an IDENTICAL ENVELOPE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LIGHTS COME ON.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb freezes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAITO (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Turn around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb turns.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At the far end of the room: Saito.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Next to him is Mal, gun in hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She smiles at Cobb.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: The gun, Dom.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb doesn't move.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mal motions outside- two GUARDS drag Arthur into the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mal puts the gun to his head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: Please.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb slowly places his gun at his end of the long table, then SLIDES it along the polished ebony.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It comes to rest HALFWAY down the length or the table.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAITO
{DIALOGUE}: Now the envelope, Mr. Cobb.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb reaches into his waistband, removes ONE of the envelopes, SLIDES it along the table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Steps back, hands raised.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Did she tell you, or have you known all along?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAITO
{DIALOGUE}: That you're here to steal from me?
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Or that we're actually asleep?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur gives Cobb an I-told-you-so look.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAITO
{DIALOGUE}: I want to know who your employer is.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mal COCKS the gun at Arthur's temple.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 9.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: No point threatening him in a dream.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: That depends on what you're threatening.
{DIALOGUE}: Killing him would just wake him up... but pain?
{DIALOGUE}: Pain is in the mind...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mal LOWERS the gun and SHOOTS Arthur in the leg- Arthur drops, SCREAMING- Mal looks at Cobb, cold.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: And, judging by the decor, we're in your mind, aren't we, Arthur?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb watches Arthur's PAIN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mal aims at Arthur's other leg...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb SPRINGS for the table, SKIDDING along its polished surface- he GRABS his gun- SHOOTS ARTHUR BETWEEN THE EYES-
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur DROPS- the room starts to SHUDDER in a MASSIVE EARTHQUAKE- Cobb SPRINGS for the door- Arthur's eyes stare at the ceiling, DEAD, and we-
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FILTHY BATHROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur's EYES OPEN as he WAKES IN THE ARMCHAIR- he GRABS at the tubes at his wrist, YANKING them free-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NASH
{DIALOGUE}: What're you doing?!
{DIALOGUE}: It's too soon-
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FLUID spurts from the tubes as Arthur STRUGGLES with the SILVER CASE on the bathroom floor.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: I know!
{DIALOGUE}: We have to reconnect the loop before they wake up!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur grabs the case and pushes through the door to the bedroom- following the tubes to where they meet Saito's wrist- SAITO LIES ON THE BED ASLEEP.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saito STIRS and we-
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. JAPANESE CASTLE CORRIDOR - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb LURCHES towards the stairs, as all around him the building BUCKS and HEAVES- 10.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. DINING ROOM, JAPANESE CASTLE - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saito and the Guards PANIC.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mal walks calmly through the destruction, picks up the envelope and turns to Saito.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: He was close.
{DIALOGUE}: Very close.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. GRAND STAIRCASE, JAPANESE CASTLE - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb runs up the stairs, pulling out the SECOND ENVELOPE-
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. DINING ROOM, JAPANESE CASTLE - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saito RIPS open the envelope, pulls out sheets of paper.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks at Mal, PANICKED.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns to the Guards-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAITO
{DIALOGUE}: Stop him!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mal, confused, looks at the sheets of paper: THEY ARE BLANK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mal smiles, amused.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. GRAND STAIRCASE, JAPANESE CASTLE - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Cobb runs up the stairs he reads the TYPEWRITTEN SHEETS from his envelope, and we-
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. DILAPIDATED HOTEL ROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur OPENS the silver case: a COMPLEX MECHANISM of TUBES, SYRINGES, DOSAGE CONTROLLERS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur's hands fly across the machine's controls as he glances at Saito's STIRRING face-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: I'm not going to make it!
{DIALOGUE}: Wake Cobb!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FILTHY BATHROOM - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nash turns to Cobb.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Raises his hand and SMACKS him across the face, and we-
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. GRAND STAIRCASE, JAPANESE CASTLE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb is SMASHED sideways off his feet... 11.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. DINING ROOM, JAPANESE CASTLE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The CEILING CRACKS above Saito- he looks up as a TON of STONE floods down, CRUSHING HIM and we-
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. DILAPIDATED HOTEL ROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saito's eyes FLICKER OPEN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AWAKE.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FILTHY BATHROOM - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nash SMACKS Cobb again-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NASH
{DIALOGUE}: He won't wake!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. DILAPIDATED HOTEL ROOM-CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur crouched by Saito, connects the second tube.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: Dunk him!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A CLICK: Arthur looks up to find Saito with a gun to his head and a finger to his lips, gesturing silence...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FILTHY BATHROOM - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nash puts his hand on Cobb's forehead and PUSHES HIM BACKWARDS- as Cobb starts to FALL BACKWARDS in the chair we are in SLOW MOTION, and we-
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. GRAND STAIRCASE, JAPANESE CASTLE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb, full speed, picks himself up, scrambling to read the last sheet of paper.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stares at it PUZZLED- bullets hit around him as the Guards race up the stairs and we-
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FILTHY BATHROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb in SLOW MOTION, hits the WATER- head THRASHING as he goes under- and we-
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. GRAND STAIRCASE, JAPANESE CASTLE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb glances up from the paper as WATER EXPLODES IN THROUGH ALL THE WINDOWS, FLOODING THE ENTIRE HALL- 12.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COBB IS SWAMPED BY WATER, SPUN IN ALL DIRECTIONS AT ONCE- HE PULLS DEEPER OR FOR THE SURFACE, WE CAN'T TELL...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HE BREAKS THE SURFACE, GASPING FOR AIR IN THE BATHTUB IN THE-
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FILTHY BATHROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb's AWAKE, GULPING AIR, getting his bearings.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saito SMASHES into the room, KNOCKING Nash down- Cobb LAUNCHES himself out of the tub, FLYING dripping wet across the room to SLAM Saito against the door- the gun DROPS, Cobb's fist CONNECTS with Saito's jaw and the struggle is over.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. DILAPIDATED HOTEL ROOM - MOMENTS LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb, wet but composed, sits, turning Saito's gun in his hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nash holds Saito's arms behind him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Outside, the sounds of RIOTING grow louder.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: You came prepared.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAITO
{DIALOGUE}: I bring the gun because not even my head of security knows this apartment.
{DIALOGUE}: How did you find it?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur, at the window, looks out at the WORSENING VIOLENCE.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Hard for a man in your position to keep a love nest totally secret... particularly when there's a married woman involved.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAITO
{DIALOGUE}: She would never...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: And yet, here we are.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saito is silent.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: With a dilemma.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAITO
{DIALOGUE}: You got what you came for.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Not quite.
{DIALOGUE}: The key piece of information wasn't there, was it, Mr. Saito?
{DIALOGUE}: 13.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur looks over at Cobb, worried.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: They're getting closer, Cobb.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BULLET TRAIN COMPARTMENT - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Todashi slips a pair of HEADPHONES over Nash's ears, then pulls out an MP3 player and we-
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. DILAPIDATED HOTEL ROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saito's eyes are on the floor.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: You held something back because you knew what we were up to...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb uses the barrel of the gun to raise Saito's chin.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: So why let us in at all?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saito smiles, defiant.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: VIOLENT NOISES echo up the stairway...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAITO
{DIALOGUE}: An audition.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Audition for what?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAITO
{DIALOGUE}: It doesn't matter.
{DIALOGUE}: You failed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: I extracted all the information you had in there.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAITO
{DIALOGUE}: But your deception was readily apparent.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And we-
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BULLET TRAIN COMPARTMENT - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Todashi opens the SILVER BRIEFCASE, revealing the complex mechanism of syringes and controllers- FOUR CONTROLLERS
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DISPLAY COUNTDOWNS.
{DIALOGUE}: 14.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Todashi waits for the first countdown to hit "30," then HITS PLAY on the MP3 player- He watches Nash's sleeping face as he RAISES the volume...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Through Nash's headphones: the opening bars of Edith Piaf's "Non, je ne regrette rien," and we-
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. DILAPIDATED HOTEL ROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the distant background, strange MASSIVE low-end MUSICAL start, sounding like DISTANT HORNS...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAITO
{DIALOGUE}: So leave me and go.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: You know the corporation who hired us won't accept failure.
{DIALOGUE}: We won't last two days...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The DISTANT, SLOWED-DOWN MUSIC is becoming LOUDER, as are the SHOUTS coming up the stairs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur looks at his watch, its SLOW SECOND TICKING MARKS TIME WITH THE MASSIVE MUSIC.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: Come on, Cobb.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: So now I have to do this the old- fashioned way-
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb GRABS SAITO AND PUTS HIS HEAD TO THE FLOOR, gun pressed into his cheek.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saito looks into Cobb's eyes- sees he will pull the trigger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saito BLINKS, looks away in shame-
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: When he NOTICES SOMETHING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And starts LAUGHING.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAITO
{DIALOGUE}: I've always hated this carpet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb's eyes flick to the carpet and back.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAITO
{DIALOGUE}: It's stained and frayed in such distinctive ways...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb looks up at Nash, who shrugs, at a loss.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAITO
{DIALOGUE}: But very definitely made of wool.
{DIALOGUE}: Right now I'm lying on polyester.
{DIALOGUE}: 15.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb glares at Nash, and we-
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BULLET TRAIN COMPARTMENT - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Todashi watches the first of the countdowns hit ZERO- He looks up at Arthur, STIRRING, and we-
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. DILAPIDATED HOTEL ROOM-DAY
