{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. GREAT HALL, ÉCOLE D'ARCHITECTURE - MORNING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb, carrying a shopping bag, looks into a lecture hall: no students, just a RUMPLED PROFESSOR hunched over paperwork.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 25.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. LECTURE HALL - CONTINUOUS
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: You never did like your office.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PROFESSOR MILES looks up, squinting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Recognizes Cobb.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: No space to think in that broom cupboard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb steps down past the empty wooden rows.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: Is it safe for you to be here?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Extradition between France and the U.S. is a bureaucratic nightmare.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: I think they'd find a way to make it work in your case.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb hand Miles the shopping bag.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Can you take these back for the kids?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: It'll take more than the occasional stuffed animal to convince those children they still have a father.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: I know.
{DIALOGUE}: I thought you could talk to Marie about bringing them on vacation.
{DIALOGUE}: Somewhere I could meet-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: Why would she listen to me?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: You were married for twenty years.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: She blames me as much as you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Doesn't she understand that my kids need me?
{DIALOGUE}: 26.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, she does.
{DIALOGUE}: We all do.
{DIALOGUE}: Go back and face the music, Dom.
{DIALOGUE}: Explain what Mal did.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Be realistic, Stephen.
{DIALOGUE}: They'd never understand- they'd lock me up and throwaway the key.
{DIALOGUE}: Or worse.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: You think what you're doing now is helping your case?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Lawyers don't pay for themselves.
{DIALOGUE}: This is what I have.
{DIALOGUE}: This is what you taught me.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: I never taught you to be a thief.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: No, you taught me to navigate other people's minds.
{DIALOGUE}: But after what happened with Mal there weren't a whole lot of legitimate ways for me to use that skill.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles looks at Cobb.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: Why did you come here, Dom?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb shifts slightly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: I found a way home.
{DIALOGUE}: A job.
{DIALOGUE}: For powerful people.
{DIALOGUE}: If I pull it off, I can get back to my family.
{DIALOGUE}: But I need help.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Miles realizes something.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: My God.
{DIALOGUE}: You're here to corrupt one of my brightest and best.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
