{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ariadne nods, takes off her coat and we-
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. PENROSE STEPS - LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur leads Ariadne down some busy steps in a large glass and steel ATRIUM in an office complex.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: You're going to have to master a few tricks if you're going to build three complete dream levels.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A SECRETARY DROPS some papers as they pass...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: What sort of tricks?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They take a tight turn and continue down the next flight.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: In a dream, you can cheat architecture into impossible shapes.
{META_DATA}: (MORE)
{DIALOGUE}: 46.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: That lets you create closed loops, like the Penrose Steps.
{DIALOGUE}: The infinite staircase.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ariadne FREEZES- THEY ARE IN THE EXACT SPOT THEY STARTED DESCENDING FROM, next to the Secretary gathering her papers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ariadne puzzles at the impossible construction of the stairs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: See...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur stops her gently- they are on the highest step, with a LARGE DROP to the next step.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur gestures at the drop.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: Paradox.
{DIALOGUE}: A closed loop like this helps you disguise the boundaries of the dream you've created.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: How big do the levels have to be?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: Anything from the floor of a building, to an entire city.
{DIALOGUE}: But it has to be complicated enough for us to hide from the projections.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: A maze.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: And the better the maze-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: The longer we have before the projections catch us.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ariadne looks around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sees people LOOKING at Arthur.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: My subconscious seems polite enough.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: You wait, they'll turn ugly.
{DIALOGUE}: No one likes to see someone else messing around in their mind.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: Cobb can't build anymore, can he?
{DIALOGUE}: 47.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know if he can't, but he won't.
{DIALOGUE}: He thinks it's safer if he doesn't know the layouts.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: Why?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: He won't tell me.
{DIALOGUE}: I think it's Mal.
{DIALOGUE}: I think she's getting stronger.
