{CHARACTER_NAME}: BROWNING
{DIALOGUE}: I don't want to bother him unnecessarily but I know he-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FATHER
{DIALOGUE}: Robert!
{DIALOGUE}: I've told you to keep out the damn!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MAURICE LASHES OUT, KNOCKING things from his bedside table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A NURSE calms Maurice as Fischer crouches to retrieve a FRAMED PHOTOGRAPH.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks at the photo through the broken glass- a YOUNG BOY holds a PINWHEEL CLEARLY MADE BY A CHILD (each of the points is numbered in pen), his FATHER blows on it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BROWNING
{DIALOGUE}: Must be a cherished memory of his-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FISCHER
{DIALOGUE}: I put it by his bed.
{DIALOGUE}: He hasn't even noticed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BROWNING
{DIALOGUE}: Robert, we have to talk about a power of attorney.
