{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. WORKSHOP - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The group is back in the workshop, deep in discussion.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: My question is how we go down three layers with enough stability.
{DIALOGUE}: Three layers down a little turbulence is gonna translate into an earthquake.
{DIALOGUE}: The dreams are gonna collapse with the slightest disturbance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Yusuf clears his throat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: YUSUF
{DIALOGUE}: Sedation.
{DIALOGUE}: For sleep stable enough to create three layers of dreaming...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MAKESHIFT LAB - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Yusuf depresses a plunger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur is SLEEPING in a chair.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: YUSUF (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: We will have to combine it with an extremely powerful sedative....
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Eames SLAPS Arthur, HARD.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur does not stir.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. WORKSHOP - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur unconsciously rubs his cheek.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: YUSUF
{DIALOGUE}: The compound we'll be using to share the dream is an advanced Somnacin derivative.
{DIALOGUE}: It creates a very clear connection between dreamers, whilst actually accelerating brain function.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Buying us more time in each level.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: YUSUF
{DIALOGUE}: Brain function in the dream will be about twenty times normal.
{META_DATA}: (MORE)
{DIALOGUE}: 64.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: YUSUF (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: And when you go into a dream within that dream the effect is compounded.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: How much time?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: YUSUF
{DIALOGUE}: Three dreams... that's ten hours, times twenty, times twenty, times twenty...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EAMES
{DIALOGUE}: Math was never my strong suit.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: It's basically a week one layer down, six months two layers down-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: And ten years in the third level.
{DIALOGUE}: Who wants to spend ten years in a dream?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: YUSUF
{DIALOGUE}: Depends on the dream.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EAMES
{DIALOGUE}: It's not going to take us long to crack Fischer open once we get going.
{DIALOGUE}: We'll be out in a couple days, max.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: How do we get out once we've made the plant?
{META_DATA}: (to Cobb)
{DIALOGUE}: I hope you've got something a little more elegant in mind than shooting me in the head like last time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur tilts back in his chair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Yusuf turns to Cobb.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: A kick.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: What's a kick?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Eames slips his foot under Arthur's chair leg.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIPS it- Arthur's legs SHOOT UP INSTINCTIVELY for balance-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EAMES
{DIALOGUE}: That, Ariadne, would be a kick.
{DIALOGUE}: 65.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: That feeling of falling which snaps you awake.
{DIALOGUE}: We use that to jolt ourselves awake once we're done.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: But how are we going to feel that through the sedation?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: YUSUF
{DIALOGUE}: That's the clever part.
{DIALOGUE}: I customize the sedative...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MAKESHIFT LAB - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb, Eames and Yusuf watch Arthur, ASLEEP, in a chair.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: YUSUF (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: To leave inner ear function unimpaired...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Yusuf, with a wicked grin, slowly TIPS Arthur's chair backwards... as he falls, Arthur's body JERKS, EYES OPENING just before he HITS the floor.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. WORKSHOP - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur thinks, nodding slowly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: YUSUF
{DIALOGUE}: That way, however deep the sleep, the sleeper will still feel falling...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MAKESHIFT LAB - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Yusuf gleefully LEANS a SLEEPING ARTHUR to one side ...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: YUSUF (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Or tipping...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur goes down with a CRASH, JERKING AWAKE-
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. WORKSHOP - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur thinks this through.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: Even that won't cut through three layers of deep sleep.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: The trick is to devise a kick for each level, then synchronize them to get a snap that penetrates all three layers.
{DIALOGUE}: 66.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur looks at Cobb, getting it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: We can use the musical countdown to synchronize the different kicks.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. WORKSHOP - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ariadne comes into the darkened main space.
