{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb guides her back into the elevator.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: I wanted to know what "tests" you need to do on your own every night.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CAGE STYLE ELEVATOR - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb shuts the CAGE DOOR.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ariadne hits a button.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The elevator RISES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Through the GRILL Ariadne can see a BEACH stretching off into the distance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The elevator stops.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mal sits on the sand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beside her, the two children are crouched, away from us, building a SANDCASTLE.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: Why do you do this to yourself?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: This is the only way I can still dream.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: Is it so important to dream?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb stares at his family.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: In my dreams... we're still together.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The kids, WITHOUT TURNING AROUND, jump up and RUN AWAY.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CAGE STYLE ELEVATOR - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The elevator descends.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: But these aren't just dreams, are they?
{DIALOGUE}: They're memories.
{DIALOGUE}: You said never to use memories.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: And I shouldn't.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: You're keeping her alive.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: No. 68.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: You can't let her go.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: These are moments I regret.
{DIALOGUE}: Moments I turned into dreams so I could change them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ariadne's fingers move across the buttons- stop at the "B."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: What've you got buried down there that you regret?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb pushes her hand away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hits the third floor button.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: There's only one thing I need you to understand about me...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. KITCHEN, COBB AND MAL'S HOUSE - MOMENTS LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ariadne follows Cobb into the kitchen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A THIN MAN is there, standing by the table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He holds a FOLDED PIECE OF PAPER.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: This is your house?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Mine and Mal's.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: Where is she?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: She'd already died.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Thin Man offers Cobb the piece of paper.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A CHILD'S SHOUT- Cobb TURNS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ariadne follows his gaze to the garden.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A small blonde boy faces away from them, crouched on his haunches to look at something on the ground.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: It's James.
{DIALOGUE}: My boy.
{DIALOGUE}: He's found something.
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe a worm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A slightly older girl RUNS into view.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: And there's Philippa.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She crouches beside the boy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Their FACES ARE AWAY FROM US.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They point and discuss whatever is on the ground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 69.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: I thought about calling out, so they'd turn and smile those incredible smiles... but I'm out of time-
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Thin Man thrusts the paper into Cobb's hand.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: THIN MAN
{DIALOGUE}: Right now.
{DIALOGUE}: Or never, Cobb.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb nods, turns from the window-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Then I panic that I'll always wish I'd seen them turn, that I can't waste this chance...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb TURNS BACK to call out- but the children RACE OFF...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: But the moment's passed.
{DIALOGUE}: And whatever I do, the dream's always the same... When I'm about to call... they run.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb watches them run off, calling for grandma, FACES UNSEEN.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: If I'm going to see their faces again-I've got to get back here in the real world...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Behind him, Ariadne SLAMS the grill shut.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb TURNS.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CAGE STYLE ELEVATOR - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ariadne hits the BASEMENT button.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The elevator starts to DESCEND.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ariadne STARES, fascinated as glimpses of floors slip past: Mal's childhood bedroom, a thundering wall of freight train... The elevator STOPS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Through the grill Ariadne sees a HOTEL SUITE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She pulls open the grill, steps cautiously out into-
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ELEGANT HOTEL SUITE - CONTINUOUS (NOW NIGHT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DISHEVELED bedclothes, UPENDED room service table, STRAWBERRIES across the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A STRUGGLE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ariadne steps forwards- SMASH- she looks down to see that she has kicked over a CHAMPAGNE FLUTE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ariadne feels a draught.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The CURTAIN BILLOWS.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: What are you doing here?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ariadne TURNS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mal is there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 70.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: My name is-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: I know who you are.
{DIALOGUE}: What are you doing here?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know.
{DIALOGUE}: Trying to understand.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: How could you understand?
{DIALOGUE}: Do you know what it is to be a lover?
{DIALOGUE}: To be half of a whole?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mal moves slowly towards Ariadne...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: I'll tell you a riddle.
{DIALOGUE}: You're waiting for a train.
{DIALOGUE}: A train that will take you far away.
{DIALOGUE}: You know where you hope this train will take you, but you don't know for sure...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mal glides around Ariadne, looking her over.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: But... it doesn't matter.
{DIALOGUE}: How can it not matter to you where that train will take you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Because you'll be together.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb is standing in the elevator.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mal nods.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Looks at him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: How could you bring her here, Dom?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: What is this place?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: A hotel.
{DIALOGUE}: We spent our anniversaries in this suite.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: What happened here?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mal picks up the BROKEN STEM of a champagne flute... 71.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CAGE STYLE ELEVATOR - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb PULLS Ariadne into the elevator- Mal THROWS herself towards Ariadne- Cobb SLAMS the GRILL- Mal SMASHES against it AGAIN and AGAIN like a WILD ANIMAL- Ariadne FLINCHES-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: you PROMISED!
