{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, yeah?
{DIALOGUE}: With Mal?
{DIALOGUE}: That worked out great, didn't it, Cobb?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb grabs Arthur.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: You don't know anything about that.
{DIALOGUE}: This was the only way to do this job, Arthur.
{DIALOGUE}: I did what I had to do to get back to my children.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EAMES
{DIALOGUE}: So you led us into a war zone with no way out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: We have a way out.
{DIALOGUE}: The kick.
{DIALOGUE}: We just have to push on, do the job as fast as possible and get out using the kick.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EAMES
{DIALOGUE}: Forget it.
{DIALOGUE}: We go any deeper, we just raise the stakes.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm sitting it out on this level.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: You'll never make it, Eames.
{DIALOGUE}: Fischer's security is surrounding this place as we speak.
{DIALOGUE}: The ten hours of the flight is a week at this level-you'll never make it without getting killed.
{DIALOGUE}: Downwards is the only way forwards.
{DIALOGUE}: We have to carry on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saito groans.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb looks at him- 82.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: And we have to do it fast.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Eames and Arthur weigh this.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Eames, go get ready.
{DIALOGUE}: Arthur, let's get in there and soften him up.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BATHROOM, WAREHOUSE - LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb and Arthur, wearing BALACLAVAS, PULL the sack from Fischer's head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is chained to the radiator.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FISCHER
{DIALOGUE}: I'm insured against kidnapping up to ten million-this'll be simple-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: No, it won't.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fischer looks at Cobb, unnerved.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: In.
{DIALOGUE}: your lather's office, below the bookshelves, is his personal safe.
{DIALOGUE}: We need the combination.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FISCHER
{DIALOGUE}: I never noticed a safe-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Doesn't mean you don't know the combination.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FISCHER
{DIALOGUE}: Well, I don't.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: We have it on good authority that you do.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FISCHER
{DIALOGUE}: Whose?
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. OFFICE, WAREHOUSE - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Yusuf looks through Fischer's wallet.
