{DIALOGUE}: What is in the safe?
{DIALOGUE}: 94.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BROWNING
{DIALOGUE}: Something for you.
{DIALOGUE}: Maurice always said it was his most previous gift... a will.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FISCHER
{DIALOGUE}: Maurice's will is with Port and Dunn.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BROWNING
{DIALOGUE}: It's an alternate.
{DIALOGUE}: It supersedes the other only if you want it to.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FISCHER
{DIALOGUE}: What does it say?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BROWNING
{DIALOGUE}: It splits all the component businesses of Fischer Morrow into individual companies, transferring ownership to the boards of those companies...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FISCHER
{DIALOGUE}: Leaving me nothing?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BROWNING
{DIALOGUE}: A basic living.
{DIALOGUE}: Nothing more.
{DIALOGUE}: The entire empire would cease to exist.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FISCHER
{DIALOGUE}: Destroy my own inheritance?
{DIALOGUE}: Why would he suggest such a thing?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BROWNING
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know, Robert.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb OPENS the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur is behind him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Come to your senses?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FISCHER
{DIALOGUE}: Let us go.
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know the combination.
{DIALOGUE}: Not consciously.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb considers this.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Opens his phone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pulls out his gun.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Let's try instinctively.
{DIALOGUE}: I have someone standing in your father's office ready to tap in a combination.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He holds the phone to Fischer's mouth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 95.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: First six numbers that come into your head.
{DIALOGUE}: Right now.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FISCHER
{DIALOGUE}: I have no idea-
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb SWINGS the gun onto Browning-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: RIGHT NOW!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FISCHER
{DIALOGUE}: Five, two, eight... four, nine, one.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb lowers his weapon.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Listens to the phone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Shakes his head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Shuts the phone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: You'll have to do better.
{DIALOGUE}: Bag `em.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur puts SACKS over their heads.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. WAREHOUSE - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb and Arthur drag Fischer and Browning to the van-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FISCHER
{DIALOGUE}: We're worth much more to you alive...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur places Fischer on the back seat- uses a DROPPER to drop LIQUID onto Fischer's mask- his head SLUMPS FORWARDS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Browning" yanks the sack from his head- it is now EAMES.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EAMES
{META_DATA}: (excited)
{DIALOGUE}: His relationship with his father's much worse that we thought.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: That helps us?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur pulls a SNIPER RIFLE from a case by the van.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: The stronger the issues, the more powerful the catharsis.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb motions for Yusuf to follow his upstairs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: But how do you reconcile them if they're that estranged?
{DIALOGUE}: 96.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EAMES
{DIALOGUE}: I'm working on that.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur lines up a shot through the window-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: Well, work fast-Fischer's projections are closing in quick, we need to break out of here before we're totally boxed in...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur SHOOTS two snipers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb and Yusuf gently load Saito into the van.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He groans.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ariadne straps him in, checks his bandages.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur can't get the last sniper- he's too hidden behind a wall-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EAMES
{DIALOGUE}: Shouldn't be afraid to dream a little bigger, Arthur-
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Eames lines up a shot with a grenade launcher.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fires- the sniper EXPLODES into the air- Arthur looks at Eames.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EAMES (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Shall we?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They climb into the van-
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT./EXT. VAN ON RAINY STREETS - CONTINUOUS
