{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Shifting Fischer's antipathy from his father onto Browning should work.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EAMES
{DIALOGUE}: We need the imagery, the words...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: So you destroy his one positive relationship?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: We repair his relationship with his father and expose his godfather's true nature.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EAMES
{DIALOGUE}: Hell, we should be charging Fischer as much as Saito.
{DIALOGUE}: 97.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: What about his security?
{DIALOGUE}: It's going to get worse as we go deeper.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: We bring in Mr. Charles.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EAMES
{DIALOGUE}: Who's Mr. Charles?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: A bad idea.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Arthur, the second we approach Fischer in that hotel, they're gonna mow us down-we run with Mr. Charles like on the Stein job.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EAMES
{DIALOGUE}: So you've done it before?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: Sure.
{DIALOGUE}: But it didn't work.
{DIALOGUE}: The subject realized he was dreaming and his subconscious tore us to pieces.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Eames takes this in.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EAMES
{DIALOGUE}: You learned a lot, though.
{DIALOGUE}: Right?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{META_DATA}: (to Eames)
{DIALOGUE}: I'll need a decoy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EAMES
{DIALOGUE}: No problem.
