{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOTEL CORRIDOR - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur leads Ariadne to a particular room: 491.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ROOM 491 - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur leads Ariadne in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He opens the closet, opens the room safe, pulls our FOUR BRICKS OF PLASTIC EXPLOSIVE.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: So, if everything's correct, this room should be directly below 528.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOTEL LOBBY BATHROOM - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb looks reassuringly at Fischer.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: What do you remember from before this dream?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FISCHER
{META_DATA}: (thinking)
{DIALOGUE}: Rain... gunfire... Uncle Peter.
{META_DATA}: (looks up)
{DIALOGUE}: Christ-we've been kidnapped.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Where were they holding you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FISCHER
{DIALOGUE}: They had us... in the back of a van...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Your body's bouncing around in the back of a van right now-that explains the gravity shifts.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FISCHER
{DIALOGUE}: It was... to do with a safe... Christ, why's it so hard to remember?
{DIALOGUE}: 107.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: It's like trying to remember a dream after you've woken up.
{DIALOGUE}: It takes years of practice to do it easily.
{DIALOGUE}: So, you and Browning have been pulled into this dream so they can steal something from your mind.
{DIALOGUE}: What?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FISCHER
{DIALOGUE}: They wanted a combination to a safe... they demanded the first numbers to pop into my head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: That's them extracting a locator.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FISCHER
{DIALOGUE}: A locator?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: A number from your own subconscious.
{DIALOGUE}: It can be used any number of ways...
{META_DATA}: (thinking)
{DIALOGUE}: This is a hotel.
{DIALOGUE}: Room numbers.
{DIALOGUE}: What was the number you gave them?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FISCHER
{DIALOGUE}: 5, 2... something... it was a long number.
{DIALOGUE}: 528... 528, 4 something.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{META_DATA}: (opens phone)
{DIALOGUE}: Well, we know where to start.
{META_DATA}: (into phone)
{DIALOGUE}: Fifth floor.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ROOM 491 - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur hangs up the phone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is standing on a chair, attaching the explosives to the ceiling.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: Do you use a timer?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: No, I have to judge it myself.
{DIALOGUE}: Once you're all asleep up in room 528, I wait `til Yusuf starts his kick...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: How will you know?
{DIALOGUE}: 108.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: His music warns me it's coming, then the van hitting the barrier of the bridge should be unmistakable- that's when I blow the floor out from underneath us and we get a nice synchronized kick.
{DIALOGUE}: Too soon, and we won't get pulled out; too late and I won't be able to drop us.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: Why not?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARTHUR
{DIALOGUE}: The van will be in free fall.
{DIALOGUE}: I can't drop us with no gravity.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur finishes setting the charges.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOTEL LOBBY - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saito moves through the lobby.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Browning is coming in the other direction.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saito assumes him to be Eames.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAITO
{DIALOGUE}: I see you've changed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BROWNING
