{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: These are our children.
{DIALOGUE}: Watch.
{META_DATA}: (turns to the kids)
{DIALOGUE}: Hey, James!
{DIALOGUE}: Philippa?!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The children START TO TURN to us- BUT COBB CLOSES HIS EYES.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: They're not real, Mal.
{DIALOGUE}: Our real children are waiting for us-
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The children run off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb opens his eyes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: You keep telling yourself that but you don't believe it-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: I know it-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: And what if you're wrong?
{DIALOGUE}: What if I'm what's real?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb is silent.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: You keep telling yourself what you know... but what do you believe?
{DIALOGUE}: What do you feel?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb looks at Mal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Struggling.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Guilt.
{DIALOGUE}: I feel guilt.
{DIALOGUE}: And however confused I might get.
{META_DATA}: (MORE)
{DIALOGUE}: 134.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: However lost I might seem... it's always there.
{DIALOGUE}: Telling me something.
{DIALOGUE}: Reminding me of the truth.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: What truth?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: That you were wrong to doubt our world.
{DIALOGUE}: That the idea that drove you to question your reality was a lie...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: How could you know it was a lie?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Because it was my lie.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{META_DATA}: (realizing)
{DIALOGUE}: Because you planted the idea in my mind.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Because I performed inception on my own wife, then reaped the bitter rewards...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARIADNE
{DIALOGUE}: Why?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: We'd become lost in here.
{DIALOGUE}: Living in a world of infinite possibilities.
{DIALOGUE}: A world where we were gods.
{DIALOGUE}: I realized we needed to escape, but she'd locked away her knowledge of the unreality of this world...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSERT CUT: Mal opens the doll's house.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Takes the spinning top, lies it down in the safe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LOCKS IT AWAY.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: I couldn't make Mal understand that we needed to break free.
{DIALOGUE}: To die.
{DIALOGUE}: So I started to search our world...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb turns to Mal, but keeps talking to Ariadne...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSERT CUT: Cobb WANDERS the streets of Limbo...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: Searching for the right place in her mind... 135.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSERT CUT: Cobb stops outside the VICTORIAN HOUSE, MAL'S CHILDHOOD HOME, looking up at it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He heads inside...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: And when I found that place, that secret place where she had shut away her knowledge years before, I broke it open...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSERT CUT: Cobb looks around Mal's childhood bedroom.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Comes to the doll's house...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: I broke into the deepest recess of her mind, to give her the simplest little idea.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSERT CUT: Cobb throws open the safe doors.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sitting on the shelf of the safe is a spinning top.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On its side.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: A truth that she had once known, but had chosen to forget...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSERT CUT: Cobb picks up the totem.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He SPINS it in the safe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IT SPINS AND SPINS WITHOUT END.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb CLOSES THE DOOR of the safe...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: That her world was not real.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSERT CUT: COBB AND MAL ARRIVE AT TRAIN TRACKS CUTTING THROUGH WASTELAND.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: That death was a necessary escape.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They lie on the tracks looking into each other's eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mal is crying.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb takes her hand, reassuring.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He starts to speak-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: You're waiting for a train.
{DIALOGUE}: A train that will take you far away.
{DIALOGUE}: You know where you hope this train will take you, but you can't know for sure.
{DIALOGUE}: Yet it doesn't matter...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mal looks at him across the railroad tracks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Replies-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: Because you'll be together.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The train comes, OBLITERATING the lovers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Back in the present- Cobb looks into Mal's eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is crying.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 136.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: I never thought that the idea I'd planted would grow in her mind like a cancer.
{DIALOGUE}: That even after we woke...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSERT CUT: Cobb looks around the HOTEL SUITE, confused.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He moves to the CURTAINS... Mal is on the ledge opposite.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: You'd continue to believe that your world was not real...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Crying, Mal nods-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: That death was the only escape?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSERT CUT: Mal PLUNGES to her death.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: You killed me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cobb looks at Mal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Whispers-
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COBB
{DIALOGUE}: I was trying to save you-I'm sorry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mal comes in close to Cobb.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Looks him over.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAL
{DIALOGUE}: You infected my mind.
{DIALOGUE}: You betrayed me.
{DIALOGUE}: But you can make amends.
{DIALOGUE}: You can still keep your promise.
{DIALOGUE}: We can still be together... right here.
{DIALOGUE}: In our world.
{DIALOGUE}: The world we built together.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ELEVATOR - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur hits "Play" on his music player- Edith Piaf starts to ring out, Arthur checks his detonator and we-
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ANTECHAMBER - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Eames races back in- in the relative quiet he notices MASSIVE LOW-E MUSICAL TONES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He drops his gun and goes to Fischer's side... 137.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. DUCT SYSTEM, HOSPITAL COMPLEX - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Saito musters all his remaining strength as the guard emerges- Saito FIRES, dropping the guard, then COLLAPSES, the gun clattering to the duct floor... Saito is dead.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ANTECHAMBER - CONTINUOUS
