{DIALOGUE}: I'm sorry, Robert.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fischer stares at the rain on the water.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FISCHER
{DIALOGUE}: The will means that Dad wanted me to be my own man, not live for him.
{META_DATA}: (turns to Browning) )
{DIALOGUE}: And I'm going to, Uncle Peter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Browning nods.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wipes the rain from his face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the puddle beside them, the reflection is not Browning, but Eames.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. UNDERNEATH BRIDGE IN THE RAIN - MOMENTS LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arthur sits on the riverbank, breathing heavily.
